  <div class="content_main">

    <div class="col_left">
      <div id="trash_bin">
        <h2>DISCARD PILE</h2>
        <div class="parenthesis">
          (Drag discard films here)
        </div>

      </div>

      <div id="film_feed">

      </div>
    </div>

    <div id="radar_chart">

   <div class="instruction"> <p>Drag five films onto the graph to see what your taste in movies says about YOU</p>

   <p>[Click Chart For More Info]</p>
 </div>

      <canvas id="canvas" height="650" width="650" ></canvas>

    </div>

    <div id="like_tracker">

      <div class="like_text">
        <p>Choose</p>
        <p>Five</p>
        <p>Movies</p>
      </div>

      <div class="parenthesis">
        <p>(Drag titles on left into the chart!)</p>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div id="reset_button">
      Click to reset selections.
    </div>

  </div>

  <div class="key_dialog hidden">
    <h3>What Do The Chart Classifications Mean? (Click to close)</h3>

    <strong>Instinctive:</strong>
    <p>"Living off the land, seeking simple satisfaction and leaving little behind."</p>
    <strong>Tribalistic:</strong>
    <p>"Customs, elders and the clan--in tune with the mystical, and in harmony with nature."</p>
    <strong>Exploitive:</strong>
    <p>"In a world of haves and have-nots, it's good to be a have. No guilt, no shame"</p>
    <strong>Absolutistic:</strong>
    <p>"Bringer of order, stability, and righteousness. Principled and purposeful."</p>
    <strong>Achievist:</strong>
    <p>"Playing to win--independently pursuing the good life, and having fun doing it."</p>
    <strong>Relativistic:</strong>
    <p>"Nurturing and sharing, sensitive to the spiritual and to the internal world."</p>
    <strong>Systemic:</strong>
    <p>"Using tools and the human mind to work for the greater good."</p>

    <h3>About The App</h3>
    <p>This app is running movie plot summaries through a text analytics algorithm created by Mattias Ostmar, and classifying the plots based on keywords. The algorithm is sorting according to classifications laid out in Don Beck's Spiral Dynamics vMemes Worldview system. If you're into that kind of thing, learn more here: <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spiral_Dynamics#vMEMEs=">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spiral_Dynamics#vMEMEs=</a></p>

    <p>This app is a code school team project by students at General Assembly's NYC April 2014 WDI program. We hope you enjoy playing with it!</p>

    <h3>Click To Close Window</h3>

